2. The U.S. to notify Ecuador of the names and other details of U.S.
                        fishing boats likely to be fishing in waters off Ecuador for the rest of
                        1972;

4. The U.S. to pay a flat fee to Ecuador—which we would regard as a
                        conservation fee and Ecuador would consider a licensing fee. We estimate
                        this will come to about $150,000 for the year;

5. At an appropriate point, we would issue a statement (jointly with
                        Ecuador if possible) that a solution of the fishing dispute had been reached
                        without prejudice to the Law of the Sea position of either party;
